# French with Naya — Environment Variables
#
# This file is safe to commit. It documents what variables exist.
# Copy to .env and fill in real values locally. NEVER commit .env.
#
# Note: this is a static Astro site. There are no server-side secrets.
# The variables below are only needed if you add a Supabase backend later.
# For the current stack (Web3Forms + Cal.com), no .env file is required.

# ─── Future: Supabase (if backend is added) ───────────────────────────────────
# PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# ─── Site URL (used in sitemap and canonical URLs) ────────────────────────────
# Set this in GitHub Actions as a repository variable, not here
# PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://yourdomain.com
